Description: Bronze key-ring; flattened oval bezel with an engraved design of the hawk of Horus; in the field are the letters 'Cn. Piso'(?); the key projects from the back of the ring, and is in the form of the 'ankh'.
Bibliographic references: Finger Ring / Catalogue of the Finger Rings, Greek, Etruscan, and Roman, in the Departments of Antiquities, British Museum (1312)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Augustus Wollaston Franks
